    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>A Barrow-Warden is the restless remnant of a burial guardian. An ancient oath-keeper whose duty to protect the dead has metastasized into mindless aggression. Taller than the thralls it commands, wearing rusted chain and a burial crown of tarnished iron. It carries a frost-etched blade covered in Old NorrÅ“nt runes. Unlike the thralls, it can speakâ€”though only in accusations.</p>",
      "director": "<p>The Barrow-Warden commands the draugr thralls through the Barrow-Call malice ability. Focus DPS on the Warden firstâ€”removing it stops the thrall summons. The ongoing cold damage from Rune-Blade can stack across multiple targets, so prioritize targeted healing. Law of the Grave accusations are narrative seeds for later beats.</p>",
